# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env*
!.env.example

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# Crawler corpus inputs: hand-picked seed urls and curated local documents.
# Kept out of git — see cmd/crawler/data.example/ for the expected formats.
cmd/crawler/data/

# Generated/reviewed corpus documents (cmd/crawler -mode=generate|ingest,
# internal/scam/enrich). Kept out of git except a synthetic example and the
# directory placeholder — crawled/LLM-generated content is not exposed in the
# public repository, matching cmd/crawler/data/ above.
data/corpus/*
!data/corpus/.gitkeep
!data/corpus/example.md

# Crawler site registry: CSS selectors per host. Copy sites_local.go.example to
# sites_local.go and fill in your own entries — kept local so the specific sites
# being crawled are not exposed in the public repository.
sites_local.go

# Compound Engineering Plugin docs
docs/brainstorms/
docs/plans/
docs/guides/

# Local server artifacts
.pid*
tmp